nib.text:
A woman was killed and a man was wounded in a shooting Monday evening in north Minneapolis, police said.

MPD officers responded to a report of a shooting on the 700 block of West Broadway Avenue near Merwin Liquors around 6:30 p.m.

When officers arrived, they found a woman in her 30s deceased from her injuries. 

While investigating at the location, officers were advised a man with gunshot wounds arrived at a local hospital in critical condition. 

According to preliminary information, police believe a suspect shot the victims and fled the area on foot.

The circumstances surrounding the shooting remain under investigation.

Anyone with information is asked to contact Crime Stoppers at 1-800-222-TIPS.
